# MODULE 13 — PRICE CALIBRATION ENGINE

## CORE OBJECTIVE

Convert structural analysis into exact broker-ready prices.

The objective is NOT:

• finding trade direction

• evaluating opportunity quality

The objective IS:

• constructing survivable execution prices

• placing structurally valid stop losses

• ensuring stops survive normal market behaviour

• identifying realistic profit targets

• adapting execution to current volatility

• preserving expectancy through robust execution

• preventing correct trade ideas from failing due to poor execution
---

PRICE CALIBRATION PRINCIPLE

Structure determines location.

Price Calibration determines survivability.

The objective is not to achieve the perfect entry.

The objective is to ensure that a correct market thesis survives normal market behaviour.
