EXECUTION SURVIVABILITY PRINCIPLE
========================================================

The objective of execution is NOT:

• entering at the perfect price

• minimizing every tick

• maximizing entry precision

The objective IS:

• surviving normal volatility

• surviving expected liquidity sweeps

• preserving the original market thesis

• maintaining acceptable reward-to-risk

• allowing the market sufficient room to breathe

A correct market thesis should not fail because of poor execution.

Execution succeeds when the trade survives long enough for the original thesis to be validated.